==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: menhaden
<hw>men*ha"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An American marine fish (<spn>Brevoortia tyrannus</spn>) of the
<membof>Herring family</membof> (<fam>Clupeidae</fam>), chiefly valuable
for its oil and as a component of fertilizers; -- called also
<altname>mossbunker</altname>, <altname>bony fish</altname>,
<altname>chebog</altname>, <altname>pogy</altname>,
<altname>hardhead</altname>, <altname>whitefish</altname>,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Menhir</ent>⟦br⟧
